# Memory

Paths under `.ai/memory/`:
- `working/` — ephemeral task state (gitignored content)
- `episodic/` — completed task summaries (not full chats)
- `semantic/` — stable project facts
- `decisions/` — decision notes (sync with `docs/adr/`)
- `patterns/` — confirmed code patterns only
- `failures/` — symptoms, root causes, fixes
- `preferences/` — durable preferences

## Rules
- Read semantic + failures before repeating research
- Code beats memory when they conflict
- Do not store secrets or full chain-of-thought
- After task completion: clear working memory (`npm run ai:memory:cleanup`), promote durable facts
